snippet.textDisplay: Don’t believe everything you see, cowspiracy has some truth but they embellish a lot. Yes we do fatten cows up to kill them to survive, but we do it the best way possible. We give them a good life, feed them things they enjoy, give them enrichment and tons of space with options to do what they would in nature. And note that not all farmers are awful people who beat their cows either. It’s a livelihood, we don’t want to hurt what makes us money. The better they are treated, the better quality product you get which is better money. I personally don’t eat a lot of meat but it is an important piece in the human diet. Not trying to rag on anyone’s diets, just saying this because I am studying the human diet as well as I am an agriculture student at university.
